gh issue create --repo openclaw/openclaw --title "Feishu plugin: Duplicate messages cause duplicate responses" --body "## Bug Description

The Feishu plugin delivers the same message multiple times, causing the agent to respond multiple times.

## Evidence

When sending a message to the agent, the session log shows the same message_id appearing 4-5 times:

\`\`\`
Message ID: om_x100b5788a8b608a0b38fd972d8c0d9e
Count in session log: 4 times
\`\`\`

Each delivery triggers a new agent response, resulting in duplicate replies.

## Timeline from Session Log

| Timestamp | Event |
|-----------|-------|
| 00:08:18 | Original message received |
| 00:09:17 | Message queued again (while agent busy) |
| 00:34:19 | Message re-queued |
| 00:34:31 | Message re-queued |
| 00:34:47 | Message re-queued |

## Root Cause

The Feishu WebSocket appears to re-deliver messages that weren't acknowledged quickly enough while the agent is processing. Each re-delivery triggers a new response.

## Suggested Fix

Add message deduplication to the Feishu plugin's message handler:

\`\`\`typescript
// In monitor.ts
const processedMessages = new Set<string>();

eventDispatcher.register({
  \"im.message.receive_v1\": async (data) => {
    const event = data as unknown as FeishuMessageEvent;
    const messageId = event.message?.message_id;

    // Skip if already processed
    if (messageId && processedMessages.has(messageId)) {
      log(\`feishu[\${accountId}]: skipping duplicate message \${messageId}\`);
      return;
    }

    if (messageId) {
      processedMessages.add(messageId);
    }

    await handleFeishuMessage({...});
  },
});
\`\`\`

## Environment

- OpenClaw version: 2026.2.9
- Channel: Feishu
- Connection mode: WebSocket" --label "bug,feishu"

